The paper describes the design and implementation of a mechanical processor using nonlinear mass-spring-damper models, which falls under the category of engineering and technology (cs.ET) and mechanical engineering (cs.ME). The paper also discusses the use of logic gates and automated design strategies, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents numerical validation of the proposed approach, which involves simulation and computation, making it relevant to the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO).
